posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked: Okay, assuming that’s the case, your break is somewhere between spark 2 and spark 3.  CanCoders and the Pigeon are CTRE devices, so they won’t show up in the REV error message.  You can try to narrow it down by opening up the Phoenix Tuner app and seeing what devices show up (i.e. none == between spark 2 and cancoder 2, just cancoder2 == between cancoder 2 and spark 3).  Then it’s just a matter of inspecting the electrical wiring to see what the break may be.  Could be connectors, could be solder joints, could be internal to the cancoder (I’ve heard a few reports of cold solder joints that break on the CAN connections).
